<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="929" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d929">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.48/7</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Thurston</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 26, 6 a.m. and December 26, 1 p.m. Present condolences of
                            the Government of the United States, informing <pb facs="0921" n="755" xml:id="pg_755"/> President Cabrera that this Government desires to
                            be of any possible assistance to her sister Republic of Guatemala.</p>
                        <p>Report to Department what supplies are needed from American Red
                            Cross.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>